quran[27]{c,v,t}:
  89,24,"He says, “If only I had put forth something<i class=""s"">(good) </i>for my life.”"
  89,25,"On that day, none <span class=""h"">can punish as He punishes<sup foot_note=""81472"" class=""qiraat"">1</sup> </span>,"
  89,26,"<span class=""h"">and none can shackle as He shackles</span>."
  89,27,"O you tranquil self,"
  89,28,"return to your Lord, well pleased and well pleasing;"
  89,29,"so enter among My servants,"
  89,30,"and enter My Garden."
  90,1,"No! I swear by this city,"
  90,2,"and you<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>are free of restriction in this city."
  90,3,"By the begetter and what he has begotten—"
  90,4,"We have certainly created man in distress."
  90,5,"Does he think that no one will be able to restrain him?"
  90,6,"He says, “I have consumed <span class=""h"">stacks of<sup foot_note=""81473"" class=""qiraat"">1</sup> </span>wealth.”"
  90,7,"Does he think that no one has seen him?"
  90,8,"Have We not made for him two eyes"
  90,9,"and a tongue and two lips,"
  90,10,"and showed him the two courses{1}?",footnotes:1:Of good and evil.
  90,11,"But he did not brave the difficult route."
  90,12,"And what can make you realize what the difficult route is?"
  90,13,"<i class=""s"">(It is) </i><span class=""h"">the freeing<sup foot_note=""81475"" class=""qiraat"">1</sup> </span><span class=""h"">of</span><span class=""h"">a neck</span><i class=""s"">(from the yokes of slavery) </i><span class=""h"">,</span>"
  90,14,"<span class=""h"">or the feeding—on a day of starvation—of</span>"
  90,15,"an orphaned relative"
  90,16,"or a destitute person in the dust{1},",footnotes:1:A homeless person.
  90,17,"then becoming of those who attained faith and enjoined upon one another patience and enjoined upon one another compassion—"
  90,18,"those are the fellows of the rightness."
  90,19,"But those who denied Our revelations—those are the fellows of the ill-omened;"
  90,20,"over them is a fire with no exit."
